- ✅ Stripe Identity session (basic)
- ✅ **Age & Identity Verification (KYC)** — full driver identity verification
  - Stripe Identity hosted session: government ID (DL/passport) + selfie match + liveness check (100+ countries)
  - Webhook: `identity.verification_session.verified` → extracts verified DOB from `verified_outputs.dob`
    → sets `identity_verified`, `age_verified`, overwrites self-reported DOB with verified document value
  - Age gate: `age_verified` set from authoritative Stripe document scan, not just self-reported field
  - Admin approval hard-blocked until `identity_verified = true` (API returns 422 + frontend disables button)
  - Admin carrier queue rebuilt: full verification badge set (identity, age, DOT, MC, background, fee) per carrier
  - `POST /api/v1/stripe/identity/session` — creates session, returns redirect URL
  - `GET /api/v1/carrier/kyc-status` — returns identity + age status + check detail
  - Frontend: KYC status card in carrier Personal tab showing verified/pending/failed/review states
    with Verify Identity button (opens Stripe hosted flow), Retry on failure, handles redirect back
  - Marketing: `/carrier-trust` — 5-layer verification page (Stripe Identity, FMCSA, Checkr, Clearinghouse, Human review)

- ✅ **International Address & Identity Support** — all address/ID fields internationalised for USMCA + 50+ countries
  - New migration: `country` (ISO-2) added to `job_stops`, `carrier_profiles`; `state` widened to varchar(10) everywhere
  - `carrier_profiles`: `operating_country`, `phone_e164`, `national_id_type`, `national_id_number`,
    `dl_country`, `operating_authority_number`, `operating_authority_type`
  - `organizations`: `tax_id`, `tax_id_type` (EIN/BN/VAT/ABN/etc.)
  - `lib/countries.ts`: curated list of 55+ countries with dial codes, state/postal labels, subdivision lists (US/CA/MX),
    national ID type options per country, tax ID label per country
  - `CountrySelect` reusable component with flag emoji + ISO code
  - `AddressFields` reusable component: country-aware — shows state dropdown for US/CA/MX, free text for others;
    dynamic labels (State/Province/County/Region/Oblast); dynamic postal label (ZIP/Postal Code/Postcode/CEP/etc.)
  - Carrier Personal tab: `operating_country` selector drives all conditional logic;
    US → SSN last 4; CA → SIN + provincial ID; others → national_id_type dropdown + number field;
    full international address entry; E.164 phone field for non-US
  - Carrier DOT/Commercial tab: operating context banner (reads `operating_country` from profile);
    US → CDL Class A/B/C + USDOT + MC#; CA → Class 1–5 + NSC#; MX → Licencia Federal + Permiso SCT;
    EU/other → Category C/CE + Community Licence / TIR; all endorsements renamed to "Dangerous Goods" for international use
  - Shipper profile: all three address blocks (ship-from, registered, operating) use `AddressFields`; `biz_country`/`ops_country` added
  - Locations address book: `AddressFields` component, non-US flag shown in table, `state` no longer force-uppercased to 2 chars
  - Marketing pages document coverage tiers and per-country compliance — see Marketing / Public → International hub

